---
description: Apply coverage, lint, and static-analysis policy for code changes
globs: ["src/**/*.php", "tests/**/*.php", "composer.json", "php*.xml", "phpstan*.neon", "pint.json", ".php-cs-fixer.dist.php"]
alwaysApply: false
---

Use `.github/skills/coverage-and-lint-guard/SKILL.md`.

When code changes are involved:

- think through Pint, PHPCS, PHPStan, PHPMD, and PHP-CS-Fixer implications
- add tests that protect behavior and coverage
- keep Pint as the formatting authority when tools conflict
- keep PHPCS structural only and PHPStan at max or the strictest feasible level
- avoid new PHPStan `ignoreErrors` and PHPMD global exclusions unless they are narrow, justified, and reported in final WHAT/WHY/HOW notes
- fix real checker failures in code instead of suppressing them
- remember that CI enforces the 95% minimum statement coverage standard
